✅ Question 10: VBA Code for Cleaning Data
Here’s a VBA macro to automate cleaning:

vba
Sub CleanSalesData()
    Dim ws As Worksheet
    Set ws = ThisWorkbook.Sheets("Sheet1")
    
    ' Remove duplicates
    ws.Range("A1:F" & ws.Cells(ws.Rows.Count, "A").End(xlUp).Row).RemoveDuplicates Columns:=Array(1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6), Header:=xlYes
    
    ' Replace NA and blanks with Null
    ws.Cells.Replace What:="NA", Replacement:="", LookAt:=xlPart
    ws.Cells.Replace What:="two", Replacement:="2", LookAt:=xlPart
    
    ' Format Order_Date column
    ws.Columns("F").NumberFormat = "yyyy-mm-dd"
    
    ' Fill missing Customer_Name, Region, Product with "Unknown"
    Dim rng As Range
    For Each rng In ws.Range("A2:C" & ws.Cells(ws.Rows.Count, "A").End(xlUp).Row)
        If rng.Value = "" Then rng.Value = "Unknown"
    Next rng
    
    MsgBox "Data cleaning completed successfully!"
End Sub
